## Structure

```
src/
├── domain/        # entities, value objects, errors (no framework deps)
├── application/   # use cases (orchestrate domain via ports)
├── ports/         # interfaces (what domain needs from outside)
└── index.ts       # public API
```

## Usage

```bash
pnpm install
pnpm test       # run unit tests
pnpm build      # compile TypeScript → dist/
pnpm typecheck  # type-check without emitting
```

## Example

See `src/application/create-user.ts` for a use case that depends on `UserRepository` port.
Test (`tests/create-user.test.ts`) shows how to swap the port with an in-memory implementation.

